content: If I could give this app -100 starts I would give it, pathetic. I paid $4 to install this app and learnt that its pathetic. They dont even give basic ur, er, or sounds with words..how would kids learn? Pathetic pathetic..over all app is clumsy and its a loot from customers.

Can't say enough bad things about this app. Totally useless for practicing the phonics and helping a parent at home. You Can't even finish one set of phonics and it stops making the sound or repeating...
App doesn't work consistently. Very dissatisfied with how often I have to reset the app.
Sound cuts out after a few letters
Works great on my pixel 2xl volume works fine no problems on my end
The sound keep stopping. Is this just me? I have to restart the app every few letters. Other than that it is great just wish it would continue with the sounds.

Works great on my android phone, absolutely useless on my sons fire tablet. Gets stuck a few letters into practice and won't make any sounds. Restarting the app doesn't help either. Pretty annoyed I had to purchase it on 2 devices just to get one that works.
App gets stuck at 3 or 4 letters into the exercise.
My daughter is reading above grade level because she learned her phonograms in preschool. It's never to late to learn!!

Very disappointed that this app stops doing the audio portion aloud after about 15 phonograms. There must be some kind of bug on the android version. I have to back all the way out and restart the app in order for it to play the sounds again. It has been the same problem ever since we started using it 3 weeks ago. Very frustrating. Please fix bug. When it does work, it is good and it is nice to be able to hear the sounds. I regret I paid for this.

I was hoping to use this app for a class and as a practice tool. But after downloading it, it has not worked. There is no sound. The whole point of this app is to help with phonogram sounds. I would not recommend this app.
This was a waste of time and money. I had to download the app for a class and was unable ti use it, no sound. Needless to say I was disappointed and requested a refund.
It is an excellent resource for those who are new to teaching it, and for students to use for practicing on their own!
great for intro to or continued practice of phonograms
Has helped my daughter a lot
sound cuts out and wont play.
Keeps going mute. Waste of money
the app keeps going mute, needing to be restarted. pretty disappointing
This app freezes or gets six to eight letters in then the sound stops working. Waste of money.
This app sucks. It never works!!!! Waste of money
Sound does not work after using a few times. Don't waste your money.
This app does not give me the written phonograms.

Great concept for the so but the sounds stops working halfway through the 
list of letter which defeats the purpose. Need fixed ASAP for a paid 
product. Can't teach kids the sound of the phonograms if the audio doesn't 
work
The sound do not work

This app sucks I paid the almost 4 dollars to be able to hear the sounds to 
study for a test on phonograms and the sound keeps cutting out . Save your 
money and go with the free one.

The sound works for about 5 phonograms and then nothing. There isn't any 
distinguishing instruction between similar sounds as taught be teachers. A 
suggestion would be to list the phonograms alphabetically so they could be 
easier to find. The groupings in the app are not correlated to the way the 
kids learn them in school which is fine, but it takes forever to search all 
of the letters to select the ones I need.
The written assessment needs to allow us to manually see the letters like the Apple version.
Loved it tell the last update now the sound only works if I hit the version 10.2 button for every letter.
The audio stops after a few letters. This is quite consistent. I've tried it on two phones - Nexus 5 and Nexus 5x, Nougat and Oreo, respectively. Neither worked. Hopefully they will fix it soon.
Sound does not work most of the time. Usually after 5-8 letters it just goes silent. The idea is wonderful but truly it was a waste of my $4 as it does not work most of the time :(
Sound cut's out

The app needs improvement. Audio works but the delay is way to long from the time the phonograph shows and the sound. May need two modes but usually we use to review and my child doesn't see the letter just listening to the sound then writes the corresponding phonogram.  Also a extra button to give a clue word like er = her would be beneficial.

This application works sometimes. It is frustrating because I paid for this and the free ones actually work better. My children are being taught Spalding in school and the app was recommended by the teacher. What a disappointment and a waste of $4 it would be nice if you could actually contact the people who created this app for some help. I will check back for a response I would try taking it off my phone and reinstalling except I don't want to pay again for an app I already have
Sound constantly cuts out and doesn't work waste of my money thanks a lot. The point of the app is for the sound of the letters not just to stare at them fix this or I will chargeback
I paid 3.99 for this application and now it's free can I get refunded?
Broken. This app needs an update to fix the audio. It works for a minute but then you can't get the audio to play.
I love that you can practice listening and writing the phonemes,  but the sound on the app does not always work. This makes the app difficult to use for practice.
Great app helped me a lot to sound correctly!
Why is it sometimes no sounds
Audio stopped working several times
Please add to the app. Like markings for Spalding when it comes to words

I love that I can now use this with my flash cards. We live in Texas and Spalding is not well-known or known at all. Now I can review what my son learned over 8 years ago when he was in Franklin Elementary ...He's 17 and an excellent reader. So now its time to pass that knowledge down to my daughters little girl. Thanks Spalding for such a fantastic program.

I love this app. I have several children in a Spalding school and it would be nice to be able to have personalized lists for more than one child at a time without having to reenter the lists each time.
Love this app., but I wish you could keep the differentiated phonograms programmed for practice for the whole week.
replyContent:
Jamie, 
Thank you for your review. 
As long as you do not return to the main menu, the differentiated phonograms you selected will stay programmed.

content: This app is great. Only suggested upgrade is to make drawing letters available.  Thank you this great application.
This app is awesome for working with students who are struggling with decoding and reading!
OPR & WPR practice just became easier at home!
